results.name: a(n) = number of terms in the n-th row of A120255(n) = number of terms in A001177 equal to n.
link: T. D. Noe, Table of n, a(n) for n=1..300
example: Fibonacci(9) = 34; and the divisors of 34 are 1, 2, 17 and 34. Of these divisors, 1 and 2 divide earlier Fibonacci numbers, 17 and 34 do not. So a(9) = 2.
mathematica: f[t_] := Append[t, Select[Divisors[Fibonacci[Length[t] + 1]], FreeQ[Flatten[t], # ] &]]; Length /@ Nest[f, {}, 85] (* _Ray Chandler_, Jun 14 2006 *)
